    "body": "@karalabe right, but I think that's incorrect because logs need to be indexed to the _block_ not indexed to the _transaction_? \r\n\r\nreturn values from [eth_getFilterChanges](https://eth.wiki/json-rpc/API):\r\n`logIndex: QUANTITY - integer of the log index position in the block. null when its pending log.`\r\n\r\nSo if txn[0] has 2 logs, and txn[1] has 3 logs the proper `logIndex` values should be:\r\n> txn[0].logs[0] = 0\r\n> txn[0].logs[1] = 1\r\n> txn[1].logs[0] = 2\r\n> txn[1].logs[1] = 3\r\n> txn[1].logs[2] = 4\r\n\r\nbut instead geth returns:\r\n> txn[0].logs[0] = 0\r\n> txn[0].logs[1] = 1\r\n> txn[1].logs[0] = 0\r\n> txn[1].logs[1] = 1\r\n> txn[1].logs[2] = 2",
